# Cloudflare static-asset _redirects — route every /article/<anything>
# tap from a non-installed device to the single fallback HTML at root.
# The landing page reads the id from `window.location.pathname` and
# renders the right preview / store-redirect.
#
# Installed devices NEVER reach this rule because iOS Universal
# Links / Android App Links intercept the URL before the browser
# fetches it. This rewrite only matters when the user's device
# can't claim the link (no app, or app not yet verified).
#
# Target is intentionally OUTSIDE /article/ so Wrangler's HTML auto-
# handling (which strips /index from a target) doesn't loop the rule
# back into itself.
/article/*  /article-fallback.html  200
